## Reliability notes

The July queue backlog traced to a retry storm after a dependency timeout. The fix is already deployed and worth recording:

```js
// workers/consume.js — cap retries with jittered backoff instead of tight loops
const delay = Math.min(30_000, base * 2 ** attempt)
await sleep(delay + Math.random() * 250)
if (attempt >= MAX_ATTEMPTS) return deadLetter(msg)
```

Alerting now pages on queue *age*, not queue *depth* — depth spikes are normal during deploys, age is what customers feel.
